# ⚡ AutoClick Visual Flow Editor - Professional Desktop Automation (100% Free)

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Platform: Windows](https://img.shields.io/badge/Platform-Windows-blue.svg)](#)
[![Price: Free](https://img.shields.io/badge/Price-Free-brightgreen.svg)](#)

**AutoClick Visual Flow Editor** is a powerful, enterprise-ready desktop automation suite that lets you design, run, and manage workflows visually. Built on Python and Tkinter, it provides a high-performance visual canvas where you can build complex automation flows by connecting nodes—without writing a single line of boilerplate code.

Whether you are looking to eliminate repetitive manual tasks or bridge legacy desktop software with modern APIs, AutoClick makes automation fast, reliable, and completely free.

---

## 📸 Interface Preview

![AutoClick Visual Flow Editor Interface](printscreen.png)

---

## 🚀 Why Choose AutoClick? (Enterprise-Grade & 100% Free)

*   **Free Forever**: No subscriptions, no hidden limitations, and no licensing costs. Ideal for personal projects, startups, and enterprise environments alike.
*   **Intuitive Drag-and-Drop Canvas**: Map out your automation logic visually. Drag nodes, link them with smooth curves, and use custom routing *waypoints* to keep your flows clean.
*   **Low-Level Windows Precision**: Interacts directly with the Windows API using Python's `ctypes`. This ensures sub-millisecond click accuracy and robust keyboard typing emulation.
*   **Dynamic Variable Engine (Payload)**: Pass data smoothly from one node to the next. Variables resolved in one step (like an API response or database query result) can be interpolated in any subsequent step using simple `{node_name.property}` syntax.
*   **Built-in External Connectors**: Seamlessly execute SQL queries on PostgreSQL, MySQL, and SQLite databases, or make secure calls to external REST APIs using Bearer, Basic, or API Key authentication.

---

## 💼 What You Can Automate

### For Businesses & Teams
*   **Legacy Application Bridging**: Capture data from old desktop systems and push it to modern web databases or SaaS tools via REST APIs.
*   **Automated Database Pipelines**: Pull customer records or logs from PostgreSQL/MySQL and process them through visual loops.
*   **Scheduled Reporting & Alerts**: Run recurring queries, check for conditions, and trigger notifications or webhooks if data anomalies are detected.

### For Professionals & Individuals
*   **Repetitive Data Entry**: Simulate human speed typing, tab navigation, and clicks to populate spreadsheets, web forms, and ERPs.
*   **Interactive Testing**: Run automated QA sequences on desktop software interfaces.
*   **Global Hotkey Control**: Pause, resume, and stop executions instantly with system tray integrations and global keybinds (`F9` and `F10`).

---

## 🔮 Available Node Types

| Node Type | Category | Description | Key Properties |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Start (Início)** | Core | The entry point of the flow. Supports Single, N-times, or Infinite loops. | `loop_mode`, `loop_count` |
| **Click (Clique)** | Mouse | Simulates a precise left-click at specific coordinate points. | `x`, `y` |
| **Move Mouse** | Mouse | Moves the mouse cursor without clicking. | `x`, `y` |
| **Press Key (Tecla)** | Keyboard | Simulates keypress events (e.g., Enter, Tab, Ctrl, Shift). | `key`, `count` |
| **Type Text** | Keyboard | Types text into the active field, supporting variable placeholder rendering. | `text` |
| **Delay (Aguardar)** | Timing | Pauses workflow execution for a defined duration. | `seconds` |
| **Capture Data** | Utility | Gathers active window title, handle (HWND), and cursor type. | `capture_type` |
| **Condition (Se)** | Logic | Paths execution dynamically based on comparisons (contains, matches, etc.). | `variable`, `operator`, `value` |
| **Loop** | Logic | Iterates through array elements parsed from payloads or inputs. | `array_data` |
| **Break Loop** | Logic | Breaks out of the current active loop. | `loop_node_name` |
| **Storage Var** | Storage | Stores variables in the execution payload for later steps. | `variable_name`, `variable_value` |
| **PostgreSQL / MySQL / SQLite** | Database | Executes SQL queries directly and appends result sets to the payload. | `connection_name`, `sql` |
| **API Request** | Network | Sends HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH) with full header/body customization. | `connection_name`, `method`, `path`, `headers`, `body` |

---

## 💡 Smart Variable Interpolation (Payload Engine)

Every action executed outputs its return data to a shared payload structure. You can reference this data in subsequent nodes to create context-aware workflows.

### Example Scenario:
1.  A **Capture Data** node named `capture_window` runs and populates `{capture_window.active_window.title}`.
2.  An **API Request** node uses this value dynamically in its JSON body:
    ```json
    {
      "event": "window_change",
      "window_title": "{capture_window.active_window.title}",
      "timestamp": "{current_time}"
    }
    ```
3.  The engine automatically resolves the placeholder before sending the API request.

